pokemon.name: Bulbasaur
pokemon.desc: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokemon.

pokemon.name: Ivysaur
pokemon.desc: There is a plant bulb on its back. When it absorbs nutrients, the bulb is said to blossom into a large flower.

pokemon.name: Venusaur
pokemon.desc: By spreading the broad petals of its flower and catching the sun’s rays, it fills its body with power.

pokemon.name: Charmander
pokemon.desc: The flame on its tail indicates Charmander's life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.

pokemon.name: Charmeleon
pokemon.desc: It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.

pokemon.name: Charizard
pokemon.desc: When expelling a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.

pokemon.name: Squirtle
pokemon.desc: It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

pokemon.name: Wartortle
pokemon.desc: When tapped, this Pokémon will pull in its head, but its tail will still stick out a little bit.

pokemon.name: Blastoise
pokemon.desc: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

pokemon.name: Caterpie
pokemon.desc: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antennae on its head to drive away enemies.

pokemon.name: Metapod
pokemon.desc: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.

pokemon.name: Butterfree
pokemon.desc: It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

pokemon.name: Weedle
pokemon.desc: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.

pokemon.name: Kakuna
pokemon.desc: Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself when it is in danger.

pokemon.name: Beedrill
pokemon.desc: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

pokemon.name: Pidgey
pokemon.desc: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

pokemon.name: Pidgeotto
pokemon.desc: The claws on its feet are well developed. It can carry prey such as an Exeggcute to its nest over 60 miles away.

pokemon.name: Pidgeot
pokemon.desc: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.

pokemon.name: Rattata
pokemon.desc: Living wherever there is food available, it ceaselessly scavenges for edibles the entire day.

pokemon.name: Spearow
pokemon.desc: Very protective of its territory, it flaps its short wings busily to dart around at high speed.

pokemon.name: Pikachu
pokemon.desc: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.

pokemon.name: Raichu
pokemon.desc: When it's electricity builds, it's muscles are stimulated, and it becomes more aggressive than usual.

pokemon.name: NidoranF
pokemon.desc: Although small, its venomous barbs render this Pokémon dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

pokemon.name: Nidorina
pokemon.desc: The female has a gentle temperament. It emits ultrasonic cries that have the power to befuddle foes.

pokemon.name: NidoranM
pokemon.desc: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.

pokemon.name: Nidorino
pokemon.desc: It raises its big ears to check its surroundings. If it senses anything, it attacks immediately.

pokemon.name: Zubat
pokemon.desc: Even though it has no eyes, it can sense obstacles using ultrasonic waves it emits from its mouth.

pokemon.name: Golbat
pokemon.desc: Once it bites, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

pokemon.name: Diglett
pokemon.desc: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

pokemon.name: Psyduck
pokemon.desc: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

pokemon.name: Mankey
pokemon.desc: It’s unsafe to approach if it gets violently enraged for no reason and can’t distinguish friends from foes.

pokemon.name: Growlithe
pokemon.desc: Very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.
